Bought a non-Tesla EV and wondering which home charger to get? You're not alone — the UK's most popular electric cars are now the VW ID.3, BMW i4, Hyundai Ioniq 5, and MG4, and none of them come with a manufacturer-supplied home charger as standard.

The good news: every EV sold in the UK uses the standard **Type 2 connector**, so any home charger will physically work with any car. But "works" and "works best" are different things. Your car's onboard charger speed, its smart charging capabilities, and how you drive all affect which charger delivers the most value.

This guide gives car-specific recommendations for the UK's most popular non-Tesla EVs — covering what each car can actually handle, what the manufacturer suggests, and what we'd actually recommend based on real-world UK ownership.

<div class="callout">
<strong>⚡ Quick Answer:</strong> For most non-Tesla UK EVs, the <strong>Ohme Home Pro</strong> is our top recommendation. Its Intelligent Octopus Go integration saves £300–£500/year, the app is excellent, and it's OZEV grant eligible. If you have solar panels, the <strong>myenergi Zappi</strong> is the better choice regardless of car brand. <a href="/best-picks/best-home-ev-chargers-uk/">See our full rankings →</a>
